{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17652531","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17652531"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:37:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:37:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18540"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18540","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18540"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.27,0.21,0.03,0.48,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11272"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75602"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11272","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11272"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18540"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61120"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10858"},{"type":"tags","id":"10867"},{"type":"tags","id":"11201"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26140"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26144"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75602","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75602"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following fungi most commonly causes systemic infection in immunocompetent individuals?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Aspergillus fumigatus","Cryptococcus neoformans","Histoplasma capsulatum","Candida albicans","Mucor species"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESystemic mycoses are fungal infections that can spread throughout multiple organ systems via the bloodstream.\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003E Histoplasma capsulatum\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E is a primary pathogenic fungus that commonly causes systemic infection in immunocompetent individuals. It is found in soil contaminated with bird or bat droppings and infection typically begins with inhalation of spores. The fungus can disseminate throughout the body even in those with normal immune function.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options represent opportunistic fungi that rarely cause systemic disease in immunocompetent hosts:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003ECandida albicans\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E is part of normal human flora and typically only causes systemic infection in immunocompromised patients or those with indwelling medical devices\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003EAspergillus fumigatus\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E primarily causes invasive disease in severely immunocompromised patients, particularly those with neutropenia\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003ECryptococcus neoformans\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E mainly affects immunocompromised individuals, especially those with HIV/AIDS\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003EMucor\u003C/em\u003E species\u003C/strong\u003E cause mucormycosis, which primarily affects diabetic patients or those with compromised immune systems\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile all these fungi can cause systemic infection, \u003Cem\u003EHistoplasma capsulatum\u003C/em\u003E is unique in its ability to cause significant disease in otherwise healthy individuals.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Systemic mycoses are fungal infections that can spread throughout multiple organ systems via the bloodstream.","Primary systemic mycoses are caused by environmental fungi that typically enter through inhalation of spores.","Opportunistic systemic mycoses occur mainly in immunocompromised hosts and are caused by fungi that are often normal flora."],"references":["Mittal J, Ponce MG, Gendlina I, Nosanchuk JD. Histoplasma Capsulatum: Mechanisms for Pathogenesis. Curr Top Microbiol Immunol. 2019;422:157-191. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7212190/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61120"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18540"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61120","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61120"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-30T12:23:50+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-30T12:26:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11272"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75602"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, 